HEADWORD: Popish
<hw>Pop"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
the pope; taught or ordained by the pope; hence, of or pertaining to the
Roman Catholic Church; -- often used opprobriously.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Pop"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pop"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poplar</ent>⟦br⟧
